1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
What if I told you a single hormone controls your sodium balance?

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:05,600
Meet aldosterone.

3
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:11,600
This hormone, produced by your adrenal glands, plays a crucial role in regulating sodium levels.

4
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:18,800
When your sodium drops too low, aldosterone kicks in, signaling your kidneys to retain sodium and excrete potassium.

5
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:22,400
But here’s the twist—many factors can disrupt this balance.

6
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:26,400
Stress, diet, and even certain medications can influence aldosterone production.

7
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:32,800
Understanding aldosterone sodium isn’t just science; it’s about grasping how our bodies maintain balance amidst chaos.

8
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:36,400
Want more insights into the science of your body?

9
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:38,400
